   bio:"Dr. Wei is a Professor of Urology and a widely respected physician-scientist. He is an expert in benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH), prostate cancer screening, and health services research. His work has advanced the understanding of PSA testing and informed national guidelines. He sees patients at Ann Arbor and Brighton.",
   message:"I've spent my career developing new surgical techniques to help men with the most complex urological conditions. From urethral reconstruction to artificial sphincter placement, I treat patients who've been told their condition is too difficult. My commitment is to offer you every option and the surgical expertise to execute it.",
