   bio:"Dr. Stoffel is the Division Chief of Neurourology and Pelvic Reconstructive Surgery and an internationally recognized expert in neurogenic bladder. He has published over 110 papers and serves as a textbook editor. He specializes in complex urinary reconstruction for patients with spinal cord injury, spina bifida, and multiple sclerosis, and leads the multi-institutional Neurogenic Bladder Research Group.",
   message:"As Division Chief of Neurourology, I lead a team dedicated to the most complex voiding and pelvic floor conditions. From neurogenic bladder in spinal cord injury patients to advanced neuromodulation therapies, we handle cases that few other centers can. My commitment is to never give up on finding a solution.",
