   bio:"Dr. Bloom is a distinguished Professor Emeritus and a foundational figure in pediatric urology at Michigan Medicine. His career has been defined by leadership in congenital urologic conditions, pediatric reconstructive surgery, and the mentorship of generations of urologists. He remains active in education and scholarly work.",
   message:"Treating children requires a different kind of communication — with both the child and the parents. I take time to explain conditions in terms that families understand, address concerns honestly, and involve parents as partners in their child's care. Your child's comfort and safety are always my top priority.",
